orphan /ˈɔːfən/

(orphaned,orphans) 

1. N-COUNT An orphan is a child whose parents are dead. 孤儿 

例： ...a young orphan girl brought up by peasants. …她是由农民养大的孤儿。 

2. V-T PASSIVE If a child is orphaned , their parents die, or their remaining parent dies. 使成为孤儿 [no cont] 

例： ...a fifteen-year-old boy left orphaned by the recent disaster. …这个15岁的男孩因最近的灾难而成为孤儿。

